WEBVTT

00:12.083 --> 00:13.583
RUBY BAPTISTE:
<i>You have been lying to me.</i>

00:13.750 --> 00:15.250
<i>I wanna know everything.</i>

00:16.041 --> 00:18.375
CHRISTINA BRAITHWHITE:
<i>The whole truth</i>
<i>involves lost pages</i>

00:18.458 --> 00:20.792
from <i>The Book of Names</i>
and your family.

00:20.875 --> 00:22.083
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

00:22.375 --> 00:24.375
LETITIA LEWIS:
<i>If</i> <i>The Book of Names</i>
<i>is still out there,</i>

00:24.458 --> 00:26.792
<i>that's not just more spells,</i>
<i>that's instructions</i>

00:26.875 --> 00:27.875
<i>on how to cast them.</i>

00:28.417 --> 00:30.166
ATTICUS FREEMAN:
<i>Christina's going</i>
<i>after the pages.</i>

00:30.542 --> 00:31.875
We're gonna get
the whole damn book.

00:32.250 --> 00:34.375
SEAMUS LANCASTER:
<i>What the fuck are you doing</i>
<i>in my city, unannounced?</i>

00:34.458 --> 00:36.333
You think you can find
your stolen pages?

00:37.083 --> 00:38.709
CHRISTINA:
<i>I just want Hiram's Orrery.</i>

00:39.083 --> 00:41.417
<i>That's the key to unlocking</i>
<i>his time machine, isn't it?</i>

00:42.166 --> 00:44.083
HIPPOLYTA FREEMAN:
<i>Somethin' doesn't feel right.</i>

00:44.625 --> 00:46.125
<i>I have to get answers.</i>

00:47.792 --> 00:49.667
Mom, I don't think
we're supposed to be here!

00:50.000 --> 00:52.291
CHRISTINA:
<i>Hippolyta's had Hiram's Orrery</i>
<i>the entire time.</i>

00:52.792 --> 00:54.750
LETITIA: <i>If she's going where</i>
<i>this thing's leading her,</i>

00:54.834 --> 00:56.000
<i>she's in danger.</i>

00:56.875 --> 00:58.250
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES) ♪

01:05.250 --> 01:06.625
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

01:08.000 --> 01:09.208
[TV static drones]

01:09.291 --> 01:11.750
[bright tone]

01:12.667 --> 01:16.875
<i>[Bananarama's "Cruel Summer"]</i>

01:16.959 --> 01:21.542
[siren wailing]

01:21.625 --> 01:22.542
[horn honks]

01:22.625 --> 01:26.417
- Everyone out of the street!

01:26.500 --> 01:27.917
Please!

01:28.000 --> 01:30.792
Move out of the street!

01:30.875 --> 01:32.834
We don't wanna have to shut
this down.

01:32.917 --> 01:35.917
<i>- ♪ The air is so heavy</i>
<i>and dry ♪</i>

01:36.000 --> 01:39.750
[siren wailing]

01:39.834 --> 01:42.750
<i>♪ Strange voices are saying ♪</i>

01:42.834 --> 01:44.417
<i>- ♪ What did they say? ♪</i>

01:44.500 --> 01:47.750
<i>- ♪ Things</i>
<i>I can't understand ♪</i>

01:47.834 --> 01:49.625
<i>♪ It's too close for comfort ♪</i>

01:49.709 --> 01:52.542
<i>♪ This heat has got</i>
<i>right out of hand ♪</i>

01:52.625 --> 01:55.959
- [retches]

01:56.041 --> 01:57.583
<i>- ♪ It's a cruel ♪</i>

01:57.667 --> 02:00.125
<i>- ♪ Cruel ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ Cruel summer ♪</i>

02:00.208 --> 02:02.417
<i>['80s synth pop]</i>

02:02.500 --> 02:04.917
<i>♪ Leaving me here on my own ♪</i>

02:05.000 --> 02:06.959
<i>♪ It's a cruel ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ It's a cruel ♪</i>

02:07.041 --> 02:09.625
<i>- ♪ Cruel summer ♪</i>

02:09.709 --> 02:10.792
- All we can do is pray

02:10.875 --> 02:13.500
for the Lord to protect us
from this evil.

02:13.583 --> 02:15.125
- They are butchering
our children

02:15.208 --> 02:16.959
without consequence!

02:17.041 --> 02:19.792
My brothers and sisters,

02:19.875 --> 02:21.750
I say no more!

02:21.834 --> 02:23.625
crowd: No more!

02:23.709 --> 02:24.667
- No more!

02:24.750 --> 02:27.500
- We are all angry
over Emmett Till's murder,

02:27.583 --> 02:28.959
but we must organize

02:29.041 --> 02:31.000
and fight using the law.

02:31.083 --> 02:34.000
<i>[uneasy music]</i>

02:34.083 --> 02:38.417
[indistinct shouting]

02:38.500 --> 02:40.500
- What's that smell?

02:42.208 --> 02:43.834
- It's gotta be
one of the hottest days

02:43.917 --> 02:46.291
of the year, and...

02:46.375 --> 02:52.709
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:52.792 --> 02:54.333
- It's him, isn't it?

02:54.417 --> 02:57.375
[siren wailing]

02:57.458 --> 03:02.583
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:02.667 --> 03:05.000
- You wanna rest for a minute?

03:05.083 --> 03:06.542
We gonna be waiting
for a while.

03:06.625 --> 03:08.917
- I'm fine.
- Excuse me.

03:09.000 --> 03:10.333
- You sure?
You wanna sit?

03:10.417 --> 03:12.166
- I'm fine, Tic.

03:12.250 --> 03:15.166
- Hey.
- Oh, thank you.

03:15.250 --> 03:17.250
- Hey, boy.

03:18.542 --> 03:21.500
- Here, take mine.

03:21.583 --> 03:23.125
- Ruby.

03:24.125 --> 03:26.834
- Maybe it wasn't a good idea
to bring Dee.

03:26.917 --> 03:28.875
- Ain't no getting around this.

03:29.000 --> 03:31.542
Every Negro's rite of passage
in this country,

03:31.625 --> 03:33.375
child or not.

03:33.458 --> 03:35.792
- Uncle George would've
wanted her to see Bobo.

03:36.959 --> 03:39.333
-

03:39.417 --> 03:41.709
No more!
No more!

03:41.792 --> 03:43.083
crowd: No more!
- No more!

03:43.166 --> 03:44.542
crowd: No more!
No more!

03:44.625 --> 03:46.041
- This is a war,
and we gonna win!

03:46.125 --> 03:49.083
crowd: No more!
No more!

03:49.166 --> 03:55.792
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:55.875 --> 03:58.333
- She's seen
too much death already.

03:58.417 --> 04:00.458
We should be protecting her.

04:04.000 --> 04:05.208
- Leti, this is not the place

04:05.291 --> 04:06.667
to have
this conversation again.

04:06.750 --> 04:08.166
- It's been a week.
We need to tell her.

04:08.250 --> 04:09.834
- Her best friend just died.

04:09.917 --> 04:11.208
- Murdered.
He didn't just die.

04:11.291 --> 04:12.417
Someone did this to him.
- Okay, murdered, yes.

04:12.500 --> 04:13.417
I'm sorry. Murdered.
I know that.

04:13.500 --> 04:14.417
- And as long as we wait
to tell her,

04:14.500 --> 04:15.709
her mother's not coming back.

04:15.792 --> 04:17.083
- We don't know that for sure.
Leti--

04:17.166 --> 04:19.208
- You said there was a flash
of light from Hiram's machine

04:19.291 --> 04:20.625
and then Hippolyta disappeared.

04:20.709 --> 04:23.959
Now, what makes you think
she's coming back?

04:24.041 --> 04:25.917
<i>[ominous music]</i>

04:26.000 --> 04:28.333
- Where's Diana?

04:30.875 --> 04:33.417
- Shit.

04:33.500 --> 04:36.166
She must've snuck off
someplace.

04:36.250 --> 04:37.750
- My brothers gonna stand
right here,

04:37.834 --> 04:38.917
and I'ma stand right here!

04:39.000 --> 04:41.750
- We don't want her roaming
the streets alone today.

04:41.834 --> 04:43.125
- Go see if she's at the house.
- Okay.

04:43.208 --> 04:44.208
- I'll check mine.

04:44.291 --> 04:45.625
- I'll stay in line
in case she comes back.

04:45.709 --> 04:46.917
- Okay.

04:47.000 --> 04:49.041
- Tic.

04:49.125 --> 04:50.083
- Yeah.

04:50.166 --> 04:52.458
Yeah, I'll check
the five-and-dime.

04:52.542 --> 04:54.500
Sorry, excuse me.
Excuse me.

04:54.583 --> 04:55.792
'Scuse me. 'Scuse me.
- Sorry. 'Scuse me.

04:55.875 --> 04:57.125
- Make a hole, please.

04:57.208 --> 04:58.667
<i>- ♪ It's a cruel ♪</i>

04:58.750 --> 05:01.500
<i>- ♪ Cruel ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ Cruel summer ♪</i>

05:01.583 --> 05:03.375
<i>- ♪ Leaving me ♪</i>

05:03.458 --> 05:05.959
<i>- ♪ Leaving me here</i>
<i>on my own ♪</i>

05:06.041 --> 05:08.000
<i>♪ It's a cruel ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ It's a cruel ♪</i>

05:08.083 --> 05:10.291
<i>- ♪ Cruel summer ♪</i>
[train rumbles]

05:10.375 --> 05:12.291
<i>♪ Now you're gone ♪</i>

05:12.375 --> 05:15.333
<i>[eerie music]</i>

05:15.417 --> 05:22.375
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:24.542 --> 05:27.417
[arcade machines dinging]

05:27.500 --> 05:30.417
<i>[ominous music]</i>

05:30.500 --> 05:37.542
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:51.750 --> 05:54.458
[bell dings]

05:54.542 --> 05:57.542
[kids giggling]

06:12.917 --> 06:13.875
- [screams]

06:13.959 --> 06:16.834
- Huh?

06:16.917 --> 06:19.667
- [screams]

06:19.750 --> 06:22.333
There ain't nothing
to laugh about!

06:28.250 --> 06:30.250
[tearful laugh]

06:44.458 --> 06:47.458
[siren wailing]

06:59.667 --> 07:02.542
- Diana Freeman?

07:02.625 --> 07:04.917
I said, are you Diana Freeman?

07:05.000 --> 07:07.959
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

07:08.041 --> 07:10.583
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:10.667 --> 07:12.458
- Yes.
- This yours?

07:12.542 --> 07:14.542
- Captain won't ask you
again, girl!

07:14.625 --> 07:16.625
- Uh-huh.
Yes, it's mine.

07:16.709 --> 07:18.417
- Where's your mother?

07:18.500 --> 07:19.709
- She's on a trip for her job.

07:19.792 --> 07:22.750
- What's your mother's name?

07:22.834 --> 07:25.125
What's her name?

07:25.208 --> 07:26.709
- It's Hippolyta.

07:26.792 --> 07:28.417
- Hippo-what?

07:28.500 --> 07:30.000
Niggers and these
African names.

07:30.083 --> 07:32.375
- Where'd she go on this trip?

07:32.458 --> 07:34.625
- She, um...

07:34.709 --> 07:35.959
didn't tell me.

07:36.041 --> 07:40.041
- Your mother been
acting strange lately?

07:40.125 --> 07:43.375
- Kind of.

07:44.166 --> 07:46.250
- What do you know about magic?

07:48.375 --> 07:52.375
- Like in fantasy books?

07:52.458 --> 07:56.500
- [laughs]

07:56.583 --> 07:58.917
- [whimpers]
[screams]

07:59.000 --> 08:01.125
- [speaking Language of Adam]
- Help! Help!

08:01.208 --> 08:02.792
Let me go!

08:02.875 --> 08:07.125
- [speaking Language of Adam]

08:07.208 --> 08:08.750
[hawks, spits]

08:08.834 --> 08:12.291
[speaking Language of Adam]

08:12.375 --> 08:13.375
- [grunts]

08:13.458 --> 08:17.583
- [speaking Language of Adam]
[flies buzzing]

08:17.667 --> 08:19.917
- [coughing]

08:20.000 --> 08:23.166
I can't--I can't bre--
I can't breathe!

08:23.250 --> 08:25.542
- [speaking Language of Adam]

08:25.625 --> 08:28.542
[voice distorting]

08:28.625 --> 08:35.625
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:37.542 --> 08:40.458
- [gasping]

08:40.542 --> 08:47.542
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:05.250 --> 09:06.625
- Dee?

09:11.917 --> 09:13.500
Diana!

09:19.792 --> 09:22.750
<i>[uneasy music]</i>

09:22.834 --> 09:24.542
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:24.625 --> 09:25.834
Are you looking for a room?

09:25.917 --> 09:28.041
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:28.125 --> 09:29.417
- I'm looking for Atticus.

09:29.500 --> 09:36.500
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:43.291 --> 09:46.542
- Can't remember the last time
someone made me wait.

09:50.000 --> 09:52.375
At least I had family
to keep me company.

09:56.834 --> 09:59.083
- Teach me how to cast a spell.

09:59.166 --> 10:00.792
- You had my card
for a very long time.

10:00.875 --> 10:02.625
Why now?

10:02.709 --> 10:03.750
- It's my birthright.

10:03.834 --> 10:06.667
- [laughs]

10:08.166 --> 10:09.750
You don't have
enough whiteness in you

10:09.834 --> 10:11.583
to sell that entitlement.

10:11.667 --> 10:15.417
<i>[mysterious music]</i>

10:17.500 --> 10:20.375
No.
Something's changed.

10:20.458 --> 10:22.792
You're desperate now.
To do what?

10:22.875 --> 10:26.333
To...protect yourself?

10:26.417 --> 10:31.291
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:31.375 --> 10:33.625
You managed to get
Titus's pages.

10:33.709 --> 10:35.625
Congratulations.

10:35.709 --> 10:37.250
I wasn't sure
you could pull it off.

10:37.333 --> 10:38.333
People have died trying.

10:38.417 --> 10:40.792
I hear Hiram lost an arm.

10:40.875 --> 10:43.208
- Horatio's stolen pages
are still out there.

10:45.834 --> 10:48.333
I'd give you the orrery, but...

10:48.417 --> 10:51.333
I think what you really want
is this.

10:51.417 --> 10:56.834
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:56.917 --> 10:58.834
- An incantation isn't a spell.

11:01.375 --> 11:02.458
The words aren't enough.

11:02.542 --> 11:04.959
To cast, you need energy,

11:05.041 --> 11:06.750
intention,

11:06.834 --> 11:08.625
and a body.

11:08.709 --> 11:10.500
That's how you upset
the balance of nature

11:10.583 --> 11:13.000
without a disaster.

11:13.083 --> 11:15.375
Perfect alignment.

11:15.458 --> 11:22.417
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:27.291 --> 11:28.417
- What is that?

11:28.500 --> 11:30.458
- Protection symbol.

11:32.750 --> 11:33.834
Trace it around the location

11:33.917 --> 11:35.875
you're going to cast
the spell in.

11:35.959 --> 11:37.625
Geometric pattern.

11:37.709 --> 11:39.166
- What, in chalk?

11:39.250 --> 11:41.959
- Or in your blood.

11:42.041 --> 11:43.667
Either is preferable to dust.

11:43.750 --> 11:50.792
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:54.792 --> 11:56.083
Good luck, cousin.

11:56.166 --> 12:03.166
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:04.125 --> 12:05.417
- The autumnal equinox.

12:05.500 --> 12:09.583
<i>[uneasy music]</i>

12:09.667 --> 12:11.250
What's going to happen?

12:11.333 --> 12:17.875
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:17.959 --> 12:19.875
- I'm going to achieve
what no one in the Order,

12:19.959 --> 12:23.166
not even the all-powerful
Titus Braithwhite, could.

12:25.333 --> 12:26.583
Immortality.

12:26.667 --> 12:31.125
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:31.208 --> 12:32.750
- Dee, where the hell you been?

12:32.834 --> 12:35.125
Everybody's out
looking for you.

12:35.208 --> 12:37.041
- I ain't gotta
tell you nothing!

12:37.125 --> 12:39.583
You ain't my pops!
He's dead!

12:39.667 --> 12:42.041
So is my mama dead too?

12:42.125 --> 12:43.250
- Dee, your mama's
on a "Guide" trip.

12:43.333 --> 12:44.458
- Where is she?

12:44.542 --> 12:46.542
- On a "Guide" trip!

12:46.625 --> 12:48.709
- You're lying.

12:48.792 --> 12:51.250
She has to know about Bobo.
She'd come back.

12:51.333 --> 12:52.375
- She will, Dee, soon.

12:52.458 --> 12:54.917
- Stop fucking lying to me!

12:55.000 --> 12:57.750
You're all lying to me!

12:57.834 --> 12:58.792
- Hey.

12:58.875 --> 13:00.625
Dee.

13:00.709 --> 13:01.917
Open this damn door, Dee!

13:02.000 --> 13:03.709
Get your ass out here now!

13:07.041 --> 13:09.417
Dee!

13:09.500 --> 13:12.500
- [sobbing]

13:15.250 --> 13:16.917
- Diana, I know how you feel.

13:18.875 --> 13:23.458
When I was your age,
they took my best friend too.

13:23.542 --> 13:27.250
Thought that was
the worst of it, you know?

13:27.333 --> 13:29.709
But white folks,
they just keep coming.

13:32.250 --> 13:34.667
More vicious and evil
than the last time.

13:34.750 --> 13:35.667
<i>[radio crackles]</i>

13:35.750 --> 13:38.667
<i>[upbeat music on radio]</i>

13:38.750 --> 13:40.333
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:40.417 --> 13:42.834
You know, your pops and I,
we learned early on.

13:44.750 --> 13:46.500
No matter what you do
or how well you do it,

13:46.583 --> 13:47.792
they always take it from us.

13:47.875 --> 13:49.083
<i>- ♪ Stop that knocking</i>
<i>at the door ♪</i>

13:49.166 --> 13:50.834
<i>- ♪ Let me in ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ Stop that knocking ♪</i>

13:50.917 --> 13:53.000
<i>- ♪ Let me in ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ Stop that knocking ♪</i>

13:53.083 --> 13:56.125
- It doesn't mean you have
to give it to 'em easy.

13:56.208 --> 13:57.333
<i>- ♪ Let me in ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ Stop that knocking ♪</i>

13:57.417 --> 13:58.959
- You hear me, Dee?
<i>- ♪ Stop that knocking ♪</i>

13:59.041 --> 14:00.750
- They come for you,

14:00.834 --> 14:02.250
you damn sure make 'em work
for it!

14:03.583 --> 14:05.166
<i>- ♪ Stop that knocking,</i>
<i>stop that knocking ♪</i>

14:05.250 --> 14:06.625
- Dee?

14:06.709 --> 14:08.333
I'm coming in, okay, baby?

14:08.417 --> 14:09.333
<i>- ♪ Let me in ♪</i>
<i>[radio crackles]</i>

14:09.417 --> 14:12.041
<i>- ♪ Yeah, come on</i>
<i>and love me baby ♪</i>

14:12.125 --> 14:15.500
<i>♪ It will always be that way,</i>
<i>yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah ♪</i>

14:15.583 --> 14:18.333
<i>[upbeat music on radio]</i>

14:18.417 --> 14:21.041
<i>[disquieting music]</i>

14:37.959 --> 14:41.041
- Hey!

14:41.125 --> 14:43.542
You the maid?

14:43.625 --> 14:46.417
- No, I'm not the damn maid.

14:46.500 --> 14:49.000
- What'd you say?

14:49.083 --> 14:51.333
<i>[tense music]</i>

14:51.417 --> 14:52.917
Answer me.

14:53.000 --> 14:56.875
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:56.959 --> 14:59.250
- Is everything okay here?

14:59.333 --> 15:00.583
- You know her?

15:00.667 --> 15:03.375
- Yes, I do.
Is there a problem?

15:03.458 --> 15:05.417
- Not if you know her.

15:05.500 --> 15:07.375
That mess on the other side
of town's got everyone

15:07.458 --> 15:09.083
up in arms.

15:09.166 --> 15:10.667
Just making sure
none of it's finding its way

15:10.750 --> 15:12.000
to our neighborhood.

15:12.083 --> 15:15.834
- Thank you.
That's very much appreciated.

15:15.917 --> 15:18.875
<i>[somber music]</i>

15:18.959 --> 15:25.959
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:29.875 --> 15:32.250
- He looked like a monster.

15:32.333 --> 15:37.083
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:37.166 --> 15:40.083
<i>[Alice Smith's</i>
<i>"I Put a Spell on You"]</i>

15:40.166 --> 15:43.333
<i>[emotional music]</i>

15:43.417 --> 15:47.959
<i>- ♪ I put a spell on you ♪</i>

15:48.041 --> 15:50.959
<i>♪ Because you're mine ♪</i>

15:51.041 --> 15:55.041
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:55.125 --> 15:59.500
<i>♪ You better stop</i>
<i>the things you do ♪</i>

16:04.041 --> 16:07.625
<i>♪ I ain't lying ♪</i>

16:07.709 --> 16:12.041
<i>♪ You know I can't stand it ♪</i>

16:12.125 --> 16:15.417
<i>♪ You're running around ♪</i>

16:15.500 --> 16:19.625
<i>♪ You know better, daddy ♪</i>

16:19.709 --> 16:23.750
<i>♪ I can't stand it ♪</i>

16:23.834 --> 16:26.750
<i>♪ 'Cause you put me down ♪</i>

16:26.834 --> 16:31.625
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:31.709 --> 16:33.500
<i>♪ And I don't care ♪</i>

16:33.583 --> 16:36.792
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:36.875 --> 16:38.792
<i>♪ If you don't want me ♪</i>

16:38.875 --> 16:42.959
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:43.041 --> 16:47.542
<i>♪ I'm yours ♪</i>

16:47.625 --> 16:49.667
