my tail--

22:30.959 --> 22:31.959
- Shit!

22:32.041 --> 22:34.417
Ji-Ah, why are you here, then?

22:34.500 --> 22:35.875
If you don't have
any fucking answers,

22:35.959 --> 22:37.375
why are you here?

22:37.458 --> 22:41.000
<i>[somber music]</i>

22:41.083 --> 22:43.208
- Because she loves you.

22:43.291 --> 22:50.291
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:04.166 --> 23:06.583
- Our shit wasn't real.

23:09.250 --> 23:11.333
And I'm not dying.

23:11.417 --> 23:12.917
Now get the fuck out.

23:13.000 --> 23:19.750
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:20.750 --> 23:23.291
- [sighs]

23:27.291 --> 23:30.041
- What are you doing?

23:30.125 --> 23:32.166
- She needs to get
the fuck out of here.

23:32.250 --> 23:34.750
- Leti, Leti, Leti.
Leti, she's gone. She's gone.

23:34.834 --> 23:36.875
She's gone.
- Good. I'm glad.

23:36.959 --> 23:38.125
Go with her.
- Leti, stop.

23:38.208 --> 23:39.792
I'm sorry.
- No!

23:39.875 --> 23:42.417
I understand why you wouldn't
say anything when you got back,

23:42.500 --> 23:44.959
but all the shit
we done been through,

23:45.041 --> 23:46.291
I had to hear it from her?

23:46.375 --> 23:48.041
- Leti, I didn't know
what to tell you, okay?

23:48.125 --> 23:49.083
Or anybody!

23:49.166 --> 23:51.583
- You tell me
the fucking truth!

23:51.667 --> 23:53.083
- I didn't know!

23:53.166 --> 23:54.917
Leti, Leti, I didn't know
what she was

23:55.000 --> 23:56.083
or what happened to me
that night.

23:56.166 --> 23:58.291
I didn't--I didn't believe
what she said, Leti.

23:58.375 --> 23:59.625
- Well, a part of you
believed it.

23:59.709 --> 24:00.959
That's why you kept it from us.

24:01.041 --> 24:02.792
- I thought
I was protecting everyone.

24:02.875 --> 24:04.208
- Well, you done fucked up!

24:04.291 --> 24:06.291
'Cause everybody
but you done died

24:06.375 --> 24:08.083
since you been back.

24:08.166 --> 24:11.083
<i>[somber music]</i>

24:11.166 --> 24:17.083
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:17.166 --> 24:18.583
Where are you going?

24:18.667 --> 24:21.125
- I'm going to make it right.

24:21.208 --> 24:22.500
- What does that mean?

24:22.583 --> 24:24.667
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:24.750 --> 24:26.208
Atticus!

24:26.291 --> 24:28.000
What does that mean?

24:28.083 --> 24:29.458
- I'm gonna cast a spell.

24:29.542 --> 24:31.333
- Wait, what?

24:31.417 --> 24:32.583
When did you finish?

24:32.667 --> 24:35.583
- The night we found out
about Emmett.

24:35.667 --> 24:36.792
- But you don't know how.

24:36.875 --> 24:38.625
- I met with Christina today.

24:38.709 --> 24:40.917
I gave her the orrery key.
She told me how to cast it.

24:41.000 --> 24:43.583
- Have you lost your damn mind?
- Leti, move!

24:43.667 --> 24:45.750
- You can't trust Christina!

24:45.834 --> 24:47.333
And what if Ji-Ah's right?

24:47.417 --> 24:48.625
What if this is the way
that you die?

24:48.709 --> 24:50.417
- Leti, I've already made up
my mind, okay?

24:50.500 --> 24:53.250
- You don't get to make
those damn decisions

24:53.333 --> 24:55.625
by yourself anymore.

24:55.709 --> 24:57.250
There's too much at stake.

24:57.333 --> 24:59.458
- You don't think I know that?

24:59.542 --> 25:01.625
I'm doing this for us.
To protect us.

25:01.709 --> 25:04.333
Our future.

25:04.417 --> 25:06.500
We're surrounded
by monsters, Leti.

25:06.583 --> 25:08.542
I don't have a choice.

25:08.625 --> 25:13.041
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:13.125 --> 25:14.834
- Tic, please.

25:14.917 --> 25:16.333
Tic.

25:16.417 --> 25:18.542
We can figure this out
together.

25:18.625 --> 25:23.583
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:29.500 --> 25:32.000
- Of course.

25:32.083 --> 25:33.542
I'll be there soon.

25:43.709 --> 25:46.250
- A 14-year-old boy

25:46.333 --> 25:49.417
was beat and shot to death,

25:49.500 --> 25:53.333
then tied with barbed wire
by the neck

25:53.417 --> 25:55.417
to a cotton gin fan

25:55.500 --> 25:58.458
and cast into
the Tallahatchie River.

26:01.583 --> 26:03.709
- I know.

26:03.792 --> 26:06.125
- But do you care?

26:12.000 --> 26:13.291
At all?

26:19.500 --> 26:21.542
- You want me to say yes.

26:21.625 --> 26:24.709
- I don't want you
to say anything.

26:24.792 --> 26:26.667
I want you to feel

26:26.750 --> 26:29.291
what I feel right now.

26:30.083 --> 26:32.458
Heartbroken.

26:32.542 --> 26:34.083
Scared.

26:34.166 --> 26:35.792
Furious.

26:35.875 --> 26:37.125
Tired.

26:37.208 --> 26:39.750
So fucking tired

26:39.834 --> 26:43.750
of feeling this way
over and over.

26:43.834 --> 26:47.083
And I want you to feel alone

26:47.166 --> 26:49.291
and shameful,

26:49.375 --> 26:52.792
'cause I'm here, feeling this,

26:52.875 --> 26:56.250
and you will never
understand it.

26:56.333 --> 27:00.750
I want you
to feel guilty 'cause--

27:00.834 --> 27:02.875
for feeling safe

27:02.959 --> 27:06.375
next to you and your privilege.

27:06.458 --> 27:08.834
I should be on the South Side

27:08.917 --> 27:11.333
with my people,

27:11.417 --> 27:14.625
mourning a sweet little boy

27:14.709 --> 27:17.417
who was taken from us.

27:19.834 --> 27:22.583
You wanna know
why I took that potion?

27:26.041 --> 27:28.875
Because today of all days,

27:28.959 --> 27:31.333
I didn't wanna be a Black woman

27:31.417 --> 27:33.208
fucking a white man.

27:42.250 --> 27:44.458
- No.

27:44.542 --> 27:47.250
- What?

27:47.333 --> 27:49.417
- I don't care
about Emmett Till.

27:51.417 --> 27:53.834
I don't care about Roy Bryant

27:53.917 --> 27:55.500
or J.W. Milam,

27:55.583 --> 27:58.250
who'll never see justice
for what they did.

27:58.333 --> 27:59.417
I don't care

27:59.500 --> 28:01.208
that half this city's
on the brink because of it,

28:01.291 --> 28:04.542
and I don't think
that you really do either.

28:04.625 --> 28:06.000
<i>[uneasy music]</i>

28:06.083 --> 28:07.542
- [exhales sharply]

28:07.625 --> 28:10.041
- Pain.

28:10.125 --> 28:11.208
"It's like being unmade."

28:11.291 --> 28:14.000
That's what you said
about the transformation,

28:14.083 --> 28:18.208
but that's not what I saw
when I was fucking you.

28:18.291 --> 28:21.041
I saw someone being reborn.

28:21.125 --> 28:24.834
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:24.917 --> 28:26.500
You took that potion

28:26.583 --> 28:30.083
because you wanted to hide
from the fact

28:30.166 --> 28:34.166
that even on today of all days,
you were a woman

28:34.250 --> 28:36.834
who wanted what she wanted.

28:36.917 --> 28:43.917
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:53.291 --> 28:56.834
[together, echoing]
♪ Topsy with her yellow eyes ♪

28:56.917 --> 29:00.208
♪ Tries to claw
the one she spies ♪

29:00.291 --> 29:03.375
♪ Follows them
from tree to brook ♪

29:03.458 --> 29:06.333
♪ Over, under every nook ♪

29:06.417 --> 29:09.208
♪ Topsy has the wildest do ♪
<i>[disquieting music]</i>

29:09.291 --> 29:12.166
♪ She just wants to dance
with you ♪

29:12.250 --> 29:15.250
♪ Jig, jig, jig, jig, jig ♪

29:15.333 --> 29:17.083
- Leti!
Where's Tic?

29:17.166 --> 29:18.291
- I don't know.

29:18.375 --> 29:19.375
- When's he coming back?

29:19.458 --> 29:21.875
- I don't know, Diana.

29:21.959 --> 29:23.959
Go inside. Call your uncle.
Tell him you're here.

29:24.041 --> 29:26.291
[children singing indistinctly]

29:26.375 --> 29:27.458
- Wait.

